  "business_context": "Asset records track per-customer instances of products. The Product catalog says \"we sell Model X1000 Solar Panels\"; Asset records say \"Acme Corp owns 47 Model X1000 Solar Panels installed at their Cleveland facility on January 15, 2025, with serial numbers 4471-4517.\" Assets are essential for: warranty tracking (when does this specific device's warranty expire?), maintenance scheduling (when is the next preventive maintenance visit due?), case-context resolution (which device is the customer reporting an issue with?), upgrade-eligibility checks (which customers are running out-of-date firmware versions?), and renewal forecasting (what subscriptions expire next quarter?). Asset is primarily a B2B / field-service concept and rarely appears in nonprofit CRMs. When interviewing clients, surface \"Asset\" by asking whether they need to track instances of products at customer locations: physical equipment, installed software, subscription seats, leased machinery. If yes — they need Asset; if their model is purely transactional (sell a thing, ship it, done) without ongoing per-instance tracking, they don't.",
  "catalog_id": "asset",
  "common_synonyms": [
    "Installed Product",
    "Subscription Instance",
    "Equipment",
    "Customer Asset"
